h5.content-subhead Things I want to learn and build
#div-idea-projects-list.content.card-columns
  .card
    // img(src="./projects/favicon.ico" class="card-img-top" alt="Project 1")
    .card-body
      h5.card-title Rooms Booking system
      p.card-text Simple bookings app/site that helps with scheduling visitors, tracking occupancy etc.
  .card
    // img(src="./projects/favicon.ico" class="card-img-top" alt="Project 2")
    .card-body
      h5.card-title Community Gardening 
      .card-text
        p.
          Born out of my lack of knowledge around landscaping and maintaining a garden.
          This is a portal and app for neighbourhoods to sign up and drive community wide gardening.
          This will include integration with smart devices that for example can help track rainfall, level of sunshine.
          These would feed into the portal and individual garden profiles.
          Gardeners can then leverage the community to make informed decisions on building and maintaining their gardens.
          Gardens can opt-in to growing food to support the surrounding communities.
  .card
    // img(src="./projects/favicon.ico" class="card-img-top" alt="Project 3")
    .card-body
      h5.card-title Who's free? 
      .card-text
        p.
          App that helps small groups of people (like our LiveLifeCT group!) get together more often.
  .card
    // img(src="./projects/favicon.ico" class="card-img-top" alt="Project 4")
    .card-body
      h5.card-title Open Street Maps
      p.card-text Curious to play with this framework and compare with Google Maps.
      a(href='https://switch2osm.org/why-switch/' target='_blank' class="btn btn-primary") switch2osm.org
  .card
    // img(src="./projects/favicon.ico" class="card-img-top" alt="Project 5")
    .card-body
      h5.card-title R(eactive)Socket - service to service communications binary protocol
      p.card-text Never heard of this before, looks really interesting (e.g. backpressure solution is built in). My gut tells me I'll be using this framework someday soon (probably in the IoT world).
      a(href='https://rsocket.io/' target='_blank' class="btn btn-primary") rsocket.io
  .card
